      • fillService

        public Response fillService(Input data)
        Populates the server's database with generated data for the specified user name. The
        optional “generations” parameter lets the caller specify the number of generations of ancestors
        to be generated, and must be a non-negative integer (the default is 4, which results in 31 new
        persons each with associated events).
        Specified by:
        fillService in interface Service
        Parameters:
        data - the Input data for a fill operation (user name, and optionally a number of generations)
        Returns:
        the response for the associated service
